### English Title:
In Gaza, Health Sector Suffers Amid Ongoing War

### English Text Summary:
The article discusses the dire situation in Gaza's health sector, which has been severely impacted by an ongoing war for 18 months. It follows Dr. Wissam Sukkar, a general practitioner working in a Médecins Sans Frontières clinic, as she navigates the challenges of providing medical care amidst shortages of supplies and increasing patient numbers. Only 21 out of 36 hospitals are partially operational, and the blockade has drastically reduced medical supplies. The article highlights the struggles of displaced families, rising malnutrition, and the prevalence of diseases. Dr. Sukkar expresses her despair over the lack of hope and the overwhelming challenges faced by healthcare workers in Gaza.

